<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
	<id>3864</id>
	<title>Visual Editor: Pasting formatted text into the HTML editor pseudo-retains formatting</title>
	<description>
		<paragraph id="1">
			<sentence id="1.1">### Steps to reproduce the behavior
Write formatted text, copy it to the clipboard, switch to the HTML editor, paste the text in.</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.2">It looks formatted, but it's not.</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.3">Switching back to the visual editor loses the formatting.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="2">
			<sentence id="2.1">### Expected behavior
The text should appear without formatting in the HTML editor.</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.2">There could be an argument for pasting in the text with the markup, but I don't think that's necessary.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="3">
			<sentence id="3.1">### Actual behavior
The text appears with formatting, but it's actually plain text.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="4">
			<sentence id="4.1">##### Tested on Nexus 6P, Android 6.0.1 (shown on emulator below)</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="5">
			<sentence id="5.1">!</sentence>
			<sentence id="5.2">[wp-android-visual-editor-2](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/7233112/13758037/af0bc43e-e9fd-11e5-9425-bcaf12243eae.gif)</sentence>
		</paragraph>
	</description>
</bug>
